article.headline: Charleston Southern 107, Toccoa Falls 78
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Jamarco Warren scored 28 points to lead Charleston Southern to a 107-78 win over Toccoa Falls on Saturday night. Warren shot 10-for-12 from the field, including 6-for-6 from 3-point range for the Buccaneers (2-2). Omar Carter scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds. J.T. Knight had 11 points and 11 assists for Charleston Southern. Toccoa Falls (8-3) was led by Jachin Wettstone and David Gaulman, with both players scoring 19 points apiece. Wettstone also grabbed nine rebounds and blocked three shots. The Buccaneers shot 52.6 percent from the field (41-for-78) and outrebounded Toccoa Falls 52-35.
